---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`About Us — ${SITE.name}`}
  description="Two people in midlife who refused the default outcome and built a protocol, a practice, and a relationship around that refusal."
>
  <section class="page-hero on-dark">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="label">About Us</div>
      <h1>We are the experiment.<br />This is the data.</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <p class="lead">
        We built our relationship on a shared obsession with feeling our best. Our
        passion for health and vitality is one of the foundations of our marriage. We
        refuse to accept the version of midlife everyone told us to expect. That
        refusal drives everything we do. We stack. We track. And we built this
        together so you don't have to figure it out alone.
      </p>
      <p>
        The double meaning is the point. <strong>Stacked</strong> is the physique.
        <strong>Stacked</strong> is the protocol. And <strong>stacked</strong> is two
        people holding each other to the same standard — different goals, shared
        discipline. This isn't a highlight reel. It's an experiment, run in public,
        with the data shown.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="voices on-dark">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow-rule"><span class="label">Why we started</span></div>
      <div class="grid-2">
        <article class="voice">
          <h2>Todd</h2>
          <p>
            People in midlife don't need to give up on aging. The right stack —
            peptides, movement, fuel, and mindset — lets your body feel better as you
            age. There is a pathway. We're building it in public.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="voice">
          <h2>Jenn</h2>
          <p>
            People our age already come to us. They want to know what we're doing. We
            look like the fit couple — and we know something they don't. I'm a cancer
            survivor with genetic variants that predispose me to inflammation,
            autoimmune issues, and Lyme markers. Genetically the odds were stacked
            against me. If a peptide stack tips those odds back in my favor, I want to
            share that.
          </p>
          <p>
            We're also watching our aging parents struggle — a front-row seat to what
            20 years from now looks like if we don't stay strong and active. That's
            why we started.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="wrap next">
      <div>
        <h2>Where to go from here</h2>
        <p class="muted">The method lives in the Stacks. The ongoing log lives in the Experiment.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="next-ctas">
        <a class="btn btn-solid" href="/the-stacks/">Explore the Stacks →</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/the-experiment/">Read the Experiment</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero{padding:clamp(64px,9vw,110px) 0}
  .page-hero h1{margin-top:16px}
  .lead{font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(21px,2.8vw,28px);line-height:1.35}
  .voice h2{color:var(--amber);margin-bottom:16px}
  .voice p{color:rgba(250,247,242,0.82);margin-bottom:1em}
  .next{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:32px;flex-wrap:wrap}
  .next h2{margin-bottom:8px}
  .next-ctas{display:flex;gap:14px;flex-wrap:wrap}
</style>
